subSection.paragraph:
Sesquiterpenoids are a class of terpenoids with a wide range of bioactivities (
Brahmkshatriya and Brahmkshatriya, 2013
; 
Wang et al., 2005
). Farnesyl pyrophosphate (FPP, 
C
15
), biosynthesized via mevalonic acid (MVA) and 2 

C

-methyl-D- erythritol-4-phosphate (MEP) pathways, is a common precursor of all sesquiterpenoids that can be dephosphorylated to acyclic sesquiterpene or cyclized to mono-, bi-, tri-, or tetracyclic sesquiterpene core skeletons through the unique functions of sesquiterpene synthases (
Degenhardt et al., 2009
; 
Wu et al., 2006
). These core skeletons can be further modified by oxidation and glycosylation into more than 20,000 different sesquiterpenoid structures discovered in plants, animals, and microbes (CRC Press/Taylor & Francis Group, 2018).

Among the highly diverse family of sesquiterpenoids, triquinane-type sesquiterpenoids have been of interest for decades due to their unique fused tricyclopentane ring structure and potent bioactivities including cytotoxicity, antitumor, antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, antifungal, and anti-Alzheimer's disease (
Amouzou et al., 1989
; 
Chang et al., 2008
; 
Geldenhuys and Van der Schyf, 2007
; 
Grote et al., 2008
; 
Huang et al., 2016
; 
Liu et al., 2019
; 
Qiu et al., 2018
). The complex structure and numerous stereogenic centers of triquinane-type sesquiterpenoids have become a major challenge, and have prompted synthetic and bioorganic chemists to develop innovative synthetic methodologies and to invent total chemical syntheses for each triquinane (
Coates et al., 1998
; 
Geng et al., 2002
; 
Hong et al., 2013
; 
Qiu et al., 2018
; 
Weidner, 2012
; 
Wender and Dreyer, 1981
; 
Willmore et al., 1992
; 
Wu et al., 1994
). Interestingly, a sesquiterpene synthase synthesizing α- 

